FDA Pharmacogenomic Labeling (via PharmGKB)
-------------------------------------------
Underlying authority: U.S. Food & Drug Administration pharmacogenomic drug
          labeling ("Table of Pharmacogenomic Biomarkers in Drug Labeling") — the
          FDA label *content* is a U.S. Government work in the public domain
          (17 U.S.C. § 105).
Data used here: the per-(gene, drug) FDA **testing-level classification** (e.g.
          "Actionable PGx", "Testing Required") is taken from **PharmGKB's
          FDA-sourced drug-label annotations** (drugLabels download, accessed
          2026-06-11), i.e. PharmGKB's curation of the FDA labels. As a PharmGKB
          derivative, this column is governed by **CC-BY-SA 4.0** (see the PharmGKB
          entry above; share-alike honored), not by the public-domain status of
          the underlying FDA text.
Scope:    Context-only evidence layered over CPIC, never altering a finding.

"FDA" and "PharmGKB" are used here solely for source attribution. Yeliztli is an
independent project and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the U.S. FDA or
PharmGKB.

GTEx (eQTL regulatory associations)
-----------------------------------
Source:   GTEx Portal v8 (https://gtexportal.org/) — significant cis-eQTL
          variant-gene pairs + the WGS variant→rsID lookup table.
License:  GTEx **open-access summary statistics** (the eQTL association results)
          are freely available for use and redistribution. The protected
          individual-level GTEx data (WGS genotypes) is dbGaP-controlled and is
          NOT used or redistributed here — only the summary-level eQTL results.
Scope:    Per-(rsID, gene, tissue) cis-eQTL association (p-value + effect size),
          stored rsID-keyed (mapped from GRCh38 variant_id via GTEx's lookup) as a
          context-only regulatory layer — never a causal-mechanism claim and never
          ACMG evidence.
Citation: GTEx Consortium. "The GTEx Consortium atlas of genetic regulatory
          effects across human tissues." Science 369, 1318-1330 (2020).
          doi:10.1126/science.aaz1776

"GTEx" is used here solely for source attribution. Yeliztli is an independent
project and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the GTEx Consortium or the NIH.
